John Zwetsloot (born 30 January 1974) is a Swedish guitarist who previously played with black metal band Dissection.
In 1989, Dissection was looking for a final member to make the band a four-piece group.
They found Zwetsloot and Dissection was formed, then later went to play their first show in 1991.
In 1994 he was replaced by Johan Norman.
Having left Dissection after The Somberlain, he played for Nifelheim from 1994 to 1998.
He also started his own band Cardinal Sin in 1995.
The band split in 1996, but returned for sometime in 2003.

Zwetsloot was the original lead guitarist of the band The Haunted from Aug-Sept 1996.
